comments: Siakam (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Payton's (NYK) path and does not deliver the contact.
Morris Sr. (NYK) briefly grasps and then quickly releases Siakam's (TOR) shorts during rebounding.
Randle (NYK) and Anunoby (TOR) engage and disengage with one another throughout the duration of the pick.
Lowry (TOR) makes marginal contact with Randle's (NYK) arms before cleanly dislodging him of the ball thereafter.
Randle (NYK) makes marginal contact with Lowry's (TOR) backside after the release of the jump shot attempt.
Morris Sr. (NYK) makes marginal contact with Siakam's (TOR) front as drives toward the basket.
Anunoby (TOR) and Randle (NYK) engage and disengage with one another in the post. Anunoby then fronts Randle and makes marginal contact with his left arm before cleanly intercepting the pass.
Portis (NYK) goes through Lowry's (TOR) space and initiates contact to his backside.
Lowry (TOR) makes marginal contact with Morris Sr.'s (NYK) front as he dribbles toward the baseline.
Randle (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Siakam's (TOR) path after the hand-off and does not deliver the contact.
Morris Sr. (NYK) legally keeps his hand on the side of the ball as he performs the spin move during his dribble.
Randle (NYK) makes marginal body contact with Siakam (TOR) as he attempts to establish post position.
Lowry (TOR) cleanly dislodges Morris Sr. (NYK) of the ball along the sideline. After communicating with the Replay Center, the call on the floor of NYK ball was confirmed.
Payton (NYK) continues moving into Anunoby's (TOR) path after initial contact takes place and briefly engages with him, but the ensuing contact is marginal.
Lowry (TOR) cleanly strips Randle (NYK) of the ball.
Lowry (TOR) and Payton (NYK) engage and disengage in the lane during the inbound.
Randle (NYK) commits the take foul on Lowry (TOR).
Portis (NYK) makes marginal contact with Gasol's (TOR) left arm during rebounding.
Payton (NYK) places his left hand on Lowry's (TOR) backside before using his right forearm to cleanly dislodge Lowry of the ball thereafter.
